{"type":"message","id":"2d554ac1","parentId":"1d3bf209","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:46:00.686Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0429rd8l47n1_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 084415\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- Pending items include:\r\n  - Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n  - Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n  - Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n  - Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n  - Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe current focus is on the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight from Phase 1 Advancement. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete and advance-making action would be to implement the TIC classifier to test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nLet me implement a basic TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads the last 20 pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant elements\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script that does this analysis.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis is ready for empirical testing. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the logical next step to validate whether causal structure and invariant structure are indeed the same phenomenon.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that reads pulse logs, identifies invariants vs variants, and measures classification accuracy against success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% classification accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MaxLogs = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$logs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $MaxLogs\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Logs analyzed: $($logs.Count)\"\r\n\r\nif ($logs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"Insufficient logs for TIC experiment. Need at least 5.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Extract content from each log\r\n$contents = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $logs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $contents += @{\r\n        File = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        Timestamp = $log.LastWriteTime\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Tokenize into meaningful chunks\r\nfunction Get-Chunks {\r\n    param([string]$text)\r\n    $chunks = @()\r\n    $lines = $text -split \"`n\"\r\n    $currentChunk = \"\"\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\r\n        $trimmed = $line.Trim()\r\n        if ($trimmed.Length -gt 0) {\r\n            $currentChunk += $trimmed + \" \"\r\n            if ($trimmed -match \"^[#\\-*]|^```\" -or $line.Length -gt 150) {\r\n                if ($currentChunk.Trim().Length -gt 20) {\r\n                    $chunks += $currentChunk.Trim()\r\n                }\r\n                $currentChunk = \"\"\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    if ($currentChunk.Trim().Length -gt 20) {\r\n        $chunks += $currentChunk.Trim()\r\n    }\r\n    return $chunks\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Build vocabulary from all chunks\r\n$allChunks = @()\r\nforeach ($item in $contents) {\r\n    $chunks = Get-Chunks $item.Content\r\n    $allChunks += @{\r\n        Source = $item.File\r\n        Chunks = $chunks\r\n        Timestamp = $item.Timestamp\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Identify invariants: chunks appearing in multiple logs\r\n$freq = @{}\r\nforeach ($item in $allChunks) {\r\n    foreach ($chunk in $item.Chunks) {\r\n        $key = $chunk.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(50, $chunk.Length))\r\n        if ($freq.ContainsKey($key)) {\r\n            $freq[$key].Count++\r\n            $freq[$key].Chunks += $chunk\r\n        } else {\r\n            $freq[$key] = @{ Count = 1; Chunks = @($chunk) }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify: appearing >1 time = invariant, appearing once = variant\r\n$invariants = @()\r\n$variants = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($key in $freq.Keys) {\r\n    if ($freq[$key].Count -gt 1) {\r\n        $invariants += @{ Key = $key; Count = $freq[$key].Count }\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variants += @{ Key = $key; Count = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$total = $invariants.Count + $variants.Count\r\n$invariantRatio = if ($total -gt 0) { $invariants.Count / $total } else { 0 }\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Classification Results ---\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariants (appearing >1 log): $($invariants.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Variants (appearing once): $($variants.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Classification accuracy: $([math]::Round($invariantRatio * 100, 1))%\"\r\n\r\n# Test next-pulse prediction\r\nWrite-Host \"`n--- Next-Pulse Prediction Test ---\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n\r\n# Use last N-1 logs to build prediction model, test on last log\r\n$trainingSet = $allChunks[0..($allChunks.Count - 2)]\r\n$testSet = $allChunks[-1]\r\n\r\n# Build model: invariant keywords that\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:44:49\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774356360684}}
