{"type":"message","id":"cbc857f6","parentId":"db04ffcb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:46:15.235Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_msv3in76u65e_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 084516\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action identified: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n- Need to: \r\n  1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n  4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC experiment. This is a concrete, file-based task I can advance.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist that I can work with. I should:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nGiven this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I should make one concrete action that advances the TIC experiment goal.\r\n\r\nThe most immediate useful action would be to:\r\n1. Create a script or document that will implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or analyze the pulse logs to prepare for the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC classifier implementation. This would be a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (persistent) vs variant (session-specific) content\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI'll create a `tic_classifier.ps1` that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that distinguishes invariant (causal) vs variant (accidental) patterns across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` - the core implementation for the TIC experiment that will analyze pulse logs, classify invariant vs variant content, and measure accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests compression-causal duality: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinPulseCount = 5,\r\n    [float]$InvariantThreshold = 0.6,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$projectRoot = Split-Path (Split-Path $PSCommandPath -Parent) -Parent\r\n\r\n# --- Core TIC Functions ---\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseTokens {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    # Tokenize: headers, key-value pairs, significant phrases\r\n    $tokens = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract headers as high-weight tokens\r\n    $headers = [regex]::Matches($Content, '^#+\\s+(.+)$', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Multiline)\r\n    foreach ($h in $headers) { \r\n        $tokens += @{ Text = $h.Groups[1].Value.Trim(); Weight = 3.0; Type = \"header\" }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key metrics (lines with = or : patterns)\r\n    $kvMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, '^[\\s]*[-*]?\\s*([^:=]+)[:=]\\s*([0-9.]+)', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Multiline)\r\n    foreach ($m in $kvMatches) {\r\n        $tokens += @{ Text = \"$($m.Groups[1].Value.Trim())=$($m.Groups[2].Value)\"; Weight = 2.0; Type = \"metric\" }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Extract significant phrases (capitalized terms, quoted strings)\r\n    $phrases = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?:^|\\s)([A-Z][a-z]+(?:\\s+[A-Z][a-z]+){0,2})(?:\\s|$)')\r\n    foreach ($p in $phrases) {\r\n        $tokens += @{ Text = $p.Groups[1].Value; Weight = 1.0; Type = \"phrase\" }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $tokens\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseInvariants {\r\n    param([array]$Pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Build token frequency map across all pulses\r\n    $tokenFreq = @{}\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $Pulses) {\r\n        $tokens = Get-PulseTokens -Content $pulse.Content\r\n        $seen = @{}\r\n        foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n            if (-not $seen.ContainsKey($t.Text)) {\r\n                $seen[$t.Text] = $true\r\n                if (-not $tokenFreq.ContainsKey($t.Text)) {\r\n                    $tokenFreq[$t.Text] = @{ Count = 0; TotalWeight = 0.0; Weight = $t.Weight }\r\n                }\r\n                $tokenFreq[$t.Text].Count++\r\n                $tokenFreq[$t.Text].TotalWeight += $t.Weight\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    # Classify: invariant if appears in >threshold% of pulses (weighted)\r\n    $invariants = @()\r\n    $variants = @()\r\n    $pulseCount = $Pulses.Count\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($token in $tokenFreq.Keys) {\r\n        $data = $tokenFreq[$token]\r\n        $coverage = $data.Count / $pulseCount\r\n        $weightedCoverage = $data.TotalWeight / ($pulseCount * $data.Weight)\r\n        $avgCoverage = ($coverage + $weightedCoverage) / 2\r\n        \r\n        if ($avgCoverage -ge $InvariantThreshold) {\r\n            $inv\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:45:45"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":874,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 084516\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action identified: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n- Need to: \r\n  1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n  4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC experiment. This is a concrete, file-based task I can advance.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist that I can work with. I should:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nGiven this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I should make one concrete action that advances the TIC experiment goal.\r\n\r\nThe most immediate useful action would be to:\r\n1. Create a script or document that will implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or analyze the pulse logs to prepare for the experiment\r\n\r\nLet me create the TIC classifier implementation. This would be a PowerShell script that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (persistent) vs variant (session-specific) content\r\n3. Tests classification accuracy\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nI'll create a `tic_classifier.ps1` that implements the Temporal Invariance Compression experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next logical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that distinguishes invariant (causal) vs variant (accidental) patterns across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` - the core implementation for the TIC experiment that will analyze pulse logs, classify invariant vs variant content, and measure accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_