    $phrases = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?:^|\\s)([A-Z][a-z]+(?:\\s+[A-Z][a-z]+){0,2})(?:\\s|$)')\r\n    foreach ($p in $phrases) {\r\n        $tokens += @{ Text = $p.Groups[1].Value; Weight = 1.0; Type = \"phrase\" }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return $tokens\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Get-PulseInvariants {\r\n    param([array]$Pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Build token frequency map across all pulses\r\n    $tokenFreq = @{}\r\n    foreach ($pulse in $Pulses) {\r\n        $tokens = Get-PulseTokens -Content $pulse.Content\r\n        $seen = @{}\r\n        foreach ($t in $tokens) {"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":793,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 084516\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best next action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 (architecture cross-analysis) are complete\r\n- Key insight: Compression and Causal Discovery are the SAME problem\r\n- Next action identified: Implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment on pulse logs\r\n- Need to: \r\n  1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n  2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n  3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n  4. Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is to implement the TIC experiment. This is a concrete, file-based task I can advance.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist that I can work with. I should:\r\n1. Look at the existing pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier implementation\r\n\r\nGiven this is a stateless discontinuous agent, I should make one concrete action that advances the TIC experiment goal.\r\n\r\nThe most immediate useful action would be to:\r\n1. Create a script or document that will implement the TIC classifier\r\n2. Or analyze the pulse logs to prepare for the experiment\r\n\r